snippet.textDisplay: I loved Destiny during season one, but I just don't like the way content is added to the game anymore, I don't like the store items, I don't like the way that story progression occurs, I just don't like the general direction the game is, nor the game design. I wish things were easier to navigate and simplified, all these weird "quests, and bounties, and adventures" that have become "what makes destiny content" which seems really impersonal, and have broken off the interactions with characters in the game, it reminds me of when you ask someone a question and they say "google it" verses sitting down and explaining it to you, I feel that is what Destiny has done to me when it comes to content, I have to figure out what is going on without them telling me.
snippet.textOriginal: I loved Destiny during season one, but I just don't like the way content is added to the game anymore, I don't like the store items, I don't like the way that story progression occurs, I just don't like the general direction the game is, nor the game design.
